page.title: 20Credits
page.content: The Exbourne Women's Institute,who organized this section of the Domesday Project, would like to thank all the people who helped them, especially the following for their written contributions:Mrs.Vera Dyer,Mrs.Alison Joint,Major W.R.A.Kettle,Miss Amelia Trethewey,Mrs.Jean Walls,Mrs.Betty Wilkins, Mr.Michael Wilkins,Mrs Hilary Winter and Mr.Michael Winter; and also Mr.Patrick Summers and Mrs Hilary Winter for the photographs.They would also like to express their warm thanks to Mr.H.G.Morris, Headmaster of Exbourne School for the use of the computer,and to Mrs.Jan Goffey for all her generous help in teaching them how to use it.Finally they wish to thank all the people who live in the Woodhalls area for all their friendly help and readiness to supply the information that was needed.
